column4: "I Love You Porgy"
"Unedited solo piano\012"
"dougmck@pipeline.com.au              \012"
"Unedited solo piano"
"Deliberate minor 2nd dissonance on the anacrucis"
"Diatonic 4thy voicings follow melody"
"Play glissando with RH  Index and 5th finger  curled over  on notes about a 4th apart  - "
"so that fingernails play keys. Hand needs to lie over and  to the right
"both decrease in volume and in speed as you ascend"
"Have strong target to finish on - here a D - the root of the D7 chord"
"Change briefly to 'music-box' style for contrast"
"Pedal a C through all of this - even if it is quite dissonant"
"Dissonant voicing  - LH doubles melody below - RH plays all the rest"
"Same voicing follows the melody down"
"On G7(#11) an A triad is outlined with repeated notes"
"Final phrase of melody is played 'gospel style'"
"In tempo"
"A common idiom - top note of a phrase is briefly 'tremolo-ed' as octaves"
"Again that A triad over a G7(#11)"
"Poorly executed ascending C altered scale on C7 !!"
"Again a C pedal tone under altered dominant chords moving around 5th cycle"
"The final tag - same as first phrase - pedal held down  to hold final bass notes"
"Track 1"
"dougmck@pipeline.com.au"
"Unedited solo piano"
